tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: Renal function is impaired as indicated by elevated creatinine; mild hyperchloremia is also present. Other parameters, including glucose, electrolytes, liver enzymes, proteins, and lipid profile, are within normal limits. Findings suggest chronic kidney dysfunction; clinical correlation and further nephrological evaluation are recommended.
